                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the south base of the 1,000 pillared <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> inside the second <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Chandramauḷīśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Kulōttuṅga III Year 16: 1194 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>On palæographical grounds this inscription may be assigned to the 12th century. The details of date given viz., 16th year, Kumbha 2, Pūraṭṭādi correspond to 1194 A.D., January 25, Tuesday f.d.n. ·68.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This seems to record the gift of a lamp made of brass to god Āḷuḍaiya Nāyaṉār of Tiruvakkarai in Māttūr-nāḍu in Rājarāja-vaḷanāḍu in Jayaṅgoṇḍaśōḻamaṇḍalam. It mentions one Puṟaiśai Poṉṉambala-kKūtta[ṉ].</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
